page.title: 13ATTITUDES
page.content: Busy streets and cars are jammed together,but to live in Tenterden is nice. I like it because there is a lot to do and lots of nice people. I would like it more if there was a Sports Centre and I think that's what's missing. There are lots of shops and there are some nice places to visit, where you can see some nice things. In the Museum there are things about the railway where some times you can see some old steam engines. In school today apart from having to write this, we did lots of charts about how people came to school. Eight came by car, one by bicycle, three in a taxi, twelve walked and the other eleven walked unless it was raining, when they came by car.
